<p class="pageheader">Everfrost Zone Guide
<div class="pageheaderauthor">By <a href="mailto:rcjordan@charter.net">Herro</a></div>
<hr noshade/></p>
<b>08-13-2004</b> - 
Zone guide: Everfrost
<p>
Level Range: 1-30, 40-55
<p>
Everfrost is one cold zone.  Just about anything there casts mainly Cold-based spells and occasionally Fire-based ones.So make sure to have good resistances against those two elements.  Everfrost is connected to three different zones.  One is Blackbarrow, the home of the gnolls.  Another is Halas, the home of the Barbarians, and the last is Permafrost, the home of the Goblins and Vox.  The classes best able to solo in this zone are Druids, Rangers, Shamans, Necromancers, Shadowknights, and Bards.  If you are a low-level char and you don't know the zone that well, have someone walk you to Halas, and when you are there stand next to a guard and type /loc. Then write down the numbers.  But even if you're from Halas, you should still write the location numbers down so that if you do get lost you can find your way back.  If you want to go to Blackburrow and you don't know the way there, you might consider following the same procedure as above. Or if you're good at memorizing directions, ask the person who is leading you to your destination to help you learn the route.  Right now Permafrost isn't much of a place for a low-level to worry about.
<p>
Ok, now it's time to talk about gaining experience.  Don't worry about your deaths as much from lvls 1-10 because you won't have to retrieve your body until you're lvl 11.From lvls 1-6 it's best to fight skeletons, Ice goblins,polar bears, wolves, gnoll pups, wooly spiderlings, and Ice Goblin Scouts right in front of Halas.  The monsters don't have any great loot, but what you find will be decent enough for a low-level.Skeletons are know for only carrying just swords, axes, and staves with no special stats of any sort.  White Wolves are good for a Barbarian low-level quest ("Find White Wolf Pelts").  They sell for about 1 gold.  Weapons from the Skeletons can be sold to merchants for at least 1-2 gold pieces.  Wooly Spiderlings drops an item used for a low-level Shaman quest.  In return for doing this quest you get the spell "Gate," which can be used by Druids, Clerics, Shamans, Necromancers, Wizards, Enchanters, and Magicians.  The spiders also drop spiderling silk, which can be used to make bandages, or be sold to merchants for 2 silver.  Gnoll pups don't drop anything good except for Small Pouches and a very little amount of cash.  Polar Bears are also for another Barbarian low-level quest.  You must retrieve White Polar Bear Skins.  You can sell them for at least 1-2 gold pieces.
<p>
Now, let's move on to levels 6-11. Once you reach level 6, head to the tunnel that leads to BlackBurrow, There are 4 gnolls sitting there.  They give nice experience, medium cash, but no good loot.  Make sure to hunt with a healer though.  These things inflict nasty damage along with stun.  If you're a healer make sure you're with a fighter.  Loot-wise, all they drop are regular staves, swords, axes, daggers, and shields--all without any additional stats.
<p>
Now levels 11-20.  Stuff will start to get harders.  Since you're now level 11 you will have to start retrieving your body from now on.  It's time to fight Wooly Mammoths, Orcs, and higher level skeletons.  Make sure to get in a good group or you'll get trounced handily. Wooly Mammoths drop tusks that sell for 2 gold pieces.  Orcs drop maces, swords, staves, shields, and cloth armor.  None of them have any special stats but are worth some money.  Skeletons also drop weapons.  Sometimes they have a spell on them but no special stats.  Shields are common, but you won't find any clothing.
Levels 20-30 are a blast--literally  .Once you reach lvl 20 and finish all of your training, head out to the Orc Ruins.  Make sure to get 2 Healers, 2 Tanks, 1 Casters, and at least a Shadowknight.  5 orcs spawn at these ruins:  4 regular ones and 1 named one.  They drop runes, cloth armor, rusty and bronze weapons, along with weak shields.The named one drops the Rune of Ivy for Rangers. It's a Lore Item used to get the Ivy Bracelet.  Be careful and watch out for Ragnarok, though.  He has Death Touch like the Shadowknight.  He can also charm and cast disease, poison, and a many cold spells.  So make sure to get some nice resistances.
<p>
Levels 30-40.  Nothing is really available for you to kill in this zone that will give you experience
<p>
Levels 40-55 will present a tough time for you.  Your best bet is to fight Ice Giants in the cave in front of Permaforst  .Make sure to get 2 healers, 3 tanks, and 1 caster (an enchanter would be ideal).  The Giants drop bronze and steel weapons--nothing really special.  Although, they do sometimes drop a special item once in a good while.  Awesome cash can be found on these corpses.  You'll find enough platinum to at least buy a substantial amount of food and drink.  And by the time you get done hunting, you'll be so loaded with cash that your next low-level character won't have to worry about how much spells cost.


